As many as 16 people were injured on Tuesday when their taxi rolled on the Grayston Bridge in Sandton, Johannesburg, ER24 said. Paramedics found the taxi lying on its side in the middle of the road. Three other vehicles believed to have been involved in the crash were nearby. ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said: Paramedics assessed the patients and found that two had sustained moderate injuries, while 14 others had escaped with minor injuries. Meiring said the injured were treated before they were taken to various hospitals in the area. Authorities are investigating the cause of the crash.